# Global Repository Guidelines

Welcome to the repository! When using AI coding assistants (like Antigravity, Cursor, or Cline) to vibe code in this repository, strictly adhere to the following rules:

## 1. Code Commits
- ALWAYS read and follow the commit guidelines detailed in `.agents/skills/commit_message_guidelines/SKILL.md` before making any git commits.
- Ensure that the "WHY" behind code changes is thoroughly documented in the commit message body so that AI models can extract the implicit intention and architectural decisions.

## 2. General Practices
- Prioritize writing clean, maintainable, and self-documenting code.
- Whenever making architectural changes, briefly leave context in the commit history or inline comments targeting future AI context windows.
